# Credential-backed UAT (Cohort E2) — sample environment file.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.uat` at the repo root and fill in the secrets you
# want the credential smoke harness to exercise. `.env.uat` is git-ignored so
# your keys never land in a commit. The harness sources this file directly:
#
#   make uat-credential          # sources .env.uat, runs the credential smoke
#   ENV_UAT=/path/.env make uat-credential
#
# Every block is optional. A missing key/value is treated as "skip that block"
# — the harness records a SKIP row in the report with the reason. Fill in as
# little or as much as you want to cover.

# ── Cloud provider (pick one; the harness runs the FIRST configured key) ─────
#
# When a key is set the harness PATCHes the provider config, then calls
# /providers/:id/models and asserts the response includes a non-empty models
# list AND that a Test-connection failure would classify through the new
# Provider Doctor (see internal/llm/providerdoctor.go).
#OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
#ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIza...
#GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
#MISTRAL_API_KEY=...
#OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
#TOGETHER_API_KEY=...
#DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...
#GROK_API_KEY=xai-...

# ── Local model (Ollama) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The harness probes http://localhost:11434 unless SOULACY_UAT_OLLAMA_URL is
# set. Any reachable Ollama server with at least one model pulled passes the
# block. To use a different runtime that speaks the same API (LM Studio,
# vLLM), point the URL at it.
#SOULACY_UAT_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
#SOULACY_UAT_LOCAL_MODEL=llama3.2

# ── Live channel delivery ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Each channel block is independent. The harness records a SKIP row per
# channel that is missing either variable. When both are set it does a real
# send that WILL post to the destination chat/room/inbox — use test-only
# accounts.
#TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:AA...
#TELEGRAM_TEST_CHAT_ID=123456789

#SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...
#SLACK_TEST_CHANNEL_ID=C0123ABCD

#DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=...
#DISCORD_TEST_CHANNEL_ID=1234567890

# Email (SMTP). The harness needs enough config to send one message — fill in
# the same fields you'd set on the Email channel card. From must be an
# address the SMTP relay is authorized to send for.
#EMAIL_SMTP_HOST=smtp.example.com
#EMAIL_SMTP_PORT=587
#EMAIL_SMTP_USERNAME=alerts@example.com
#EMAIL_SMTP_PASSWORD=...
#EMAIL_SMTP_FROM=alerts@example.com
#EMAIL_SMTP_TLS=starttls              # `none` | `starttls` | `implicit`
#EMAIL_TEST_TO=you@example.com

# ── Scheduled run + Studio repair ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Neither test needs credentials — they run entirely against the isolated
# gateway. Present in this file so you can toggle them off if you're only
# testing channels/providers.
#SOULACY_UAT_RUN_SCHEDULE=1           # default 1 — create a one-shot agent and wait for it to fire
#SOULACY_UAT_RUN_STUDIO_REPAIR=1      # default 1 — POST /studio/build on a workflow with a preflight-fixable issue

# ── Harness overrides ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#SOULACY_UAT_PORT=18892               # port for the credential-smoke gateway (must be free)
#SOULACY_UAT_REPORT=./my-report.md    # override the report path (default .cache/uat-reports/CRED_SMOKE_<TS>.md)
